### 🆕 MODULE A — GT Group HR: Work Schedule Management
**Inspired by:** Notebook Page 1, Item #1

**Purpose:** Full HR work schedule management for all offices, verified by office managers.

**Features:**
- ✅ Define work schedule (weekly working days, weekends)
- ✅ Configure public holidays per country/office (Bangladesh, South Korea, Sri Lanka, Vietnam)
- ✅ Annual leave management per staff member
- ✅ Total working days counter (daily, monthly view)
- ✅ Overtime work tracking & plan
- ✅ Staff Attendance & Leave log
- ✅ Leave Plan (upcoming leave requests)
- ✅ **Verification:** Office Managers must approve/verify timesheets
- ✅ Import staff attendance data (CSV)

**Database Tables:**
```sql
-- Work schedule configuration per office
CREATE TABLE work_schedules (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  office_id UUID REFERENCES offices(id),
  working_days TEXT[] DEFAULT '{"Mon","Tue","Wed","Thu","Fri"}',
  work_start_time TIME DEFAULT '09:00',
  work_end_time TIME DEFAULT '18:00',
  created_by UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- Public holidays per office
CREATE TABLE public_holidays (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  office_id UUID REFERENCES offices(id),
  holiday_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  holiday_date DATE NOT NULL,
  year INTEGER NOT NULL,
  created_by UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- Staff attendance & leave
CREATE TABLE staff_attendance (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  staff_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  office_id UUID REFERENCES offices(id),
  date DATE NOT NULL,
  status TEXT CHECK (status IN ('present','absent','late','half_day','on_leave','holiday')),
  check_in TIME,
  check_out TIME,
  overtime_hours NUMERIC DEFAULT 0,
  notes TEXT,
  verified_by UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  verified_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- Leave requests
CREATE TABLE leave_requests (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  staff_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  office_id UUID REFERENCES offices(id),
  leave_type TEXT CHECK (leave_type IN ('annual','sick','emergency','unpaid','maternity','paternity')),
  start_date DATE NOT NULL,
  end_date DATE NOT NULL,
  total_days INTEGER,
  reason TEXT,
  status TEXT DEFAULT 'pending' CHECK (status IN ('pending','approved','rejected')),
  reviewed_by UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  reviewed_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);
```

**Page Route:** `/hr/schedule`  
**Access:** Super Admin (all offices), Office Manager (own office), Staff (view own record)

